This file contains the history of accumulation rate at GISP2 inferred by
Cuffey and Clow (1997) and Cuffey et al. (1995).  Accumulation rates
values were calculated de-straining the depth-age scale of Meese, Sowers,

the two references given.

This file gives three versions of the accumulation rate history. These
correspond to three different ice dynamics situations, as described in
Cuffey and Clow (1997).  Each one assumes a different value for the
retreat distance of the ice sheet margin during the deglaciation. The
three histories are high resolution versions of the ones shown in Figure 5
of Cuffey and Clow (1997). The last one (largest retreat distance) is
probably the most reasonable.

first column: the age according to Meese/Sowers, given as years before
1950 AD.

deglaciation.

deglaciation.
